{"lemma":"ظُلَّةٌ","slug":"ظُلَّةٌ","root":"ظ.ل.ل","root_slug":"ظ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظُلَّة","root":"ظلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27593"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27593","headword_ar":"ظُلَّةٌ","root":"Zl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that covers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shades,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one, overhead:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZal~apN","text_ar":"مَظَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~apN","text_ar":"مِظَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that shades one from the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~apN","text_ar":"مِظَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a covering:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroTul~apN","text_ar":"بُرْطُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) this latter word correctly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~ap","text_ar":"مِظَلَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the summer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brTl","text_ar":"برطل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing by which one is protected from the cold and the heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that protects and shades one, as a building"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cloud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first portion that shades"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a cloud"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of clouds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) accord. to Er-Rághib, mostly said of that which is deemed unwholesome, and which is disliked; whence the use of the word in the Kur vii. 170: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what shades one, of trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that forms a covering over one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shades one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suf~ap","text_ar":"صُفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (S, M, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which one protects himself from the heat and the cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, accord. to the lawyers,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zul~apu Ald~aAri","text_ar":"ظُلَّةُ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~ap","text_ar":"سُدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projecting roof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over the door of the house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of which the beams have one end upon the house and the other end upon the wall of the opposite neighbour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulalN","text_ar":"ظُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlN","text_ar":"ظِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalaAlN","text_ar":"ظَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAmato Zul~apu","text_ar":"دَامَتْ ظُلَّةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~i","text_ar":"الظِّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~i","text_ar":"الظِّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlapu","text_ar":"ظِلَالَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That whereby one shades himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of other things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbu yawomi","text_ar":"عَذَابُ يَوْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ul~api","text_ar":"الظُّلَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur. [xxvi. 189], is said to mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The punishment of the day of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds beneath which was a hot wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samuwm","text_ar":"سَمُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an overshadowing cloud, beneath which they collected themselves together, seeking protection thereby from the heat that came upon them, whereupon it covered them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they perished beneath it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbu yawomi AlS~uf~api","text_ar":"عَذَابُ يَوْمِ الصُّفَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sf","text_ar":"صف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahumo mino fawoqihimo ZulalN mina A@ln~aAri wamino taHotihimo ZulalN","text_ar":"لَهُمْ مِنْ فَوْقِهِمْ ظُلَلٌ مِنَ ا@لنَّارِ وَمِنْ تَحْتِهِمْ ظُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxxix. 18], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To them"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above them coverings of fire, and beneath them coverings"},{"kind":"text","text":"to those below them; Hell consisting of stages, one beneath another. (T, TA.) Seditions, or conflicts and factions, are mentioned in a trad. as being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zulal","text_ar":"ظُلَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", by which are meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and El-Kumeyt likens waves of the sea to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zulal","text_ar":"ظُلَل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulalN","text_ar":"ظُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chambers of a prison."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~apN","text_ar":"ظَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","Mgh","AZ","S","TA","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B8%D9%84%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"ظلة","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23396#2f47fe","body_html":"<span>الظلة: هي التي أحد طرفي جذوعها على حائط هذه الدار وطرفها الآخر على حائط الجار المقابل.</span>"}]}}